  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/6403449/" class="title-link">首先，你要学会怀疑。</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-6403449"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/30292029/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img1.doubanio.com/icon/u30292029-28.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/30292029/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">一只，</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2013-11-14"
      class="main-meta">2013-11-14 00:28:22</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_6403449_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                          怀疑一切的人唯一不能怀疑的只有正在进行这种思想活动的他自身。这也就是所谓的“我思故我在”，这个“我“，指的是思维的、心灵的我。在这种可怀疑它物的思维活动中，包含着一种人类的独立于上帝的自由。这种不能被否认的怀疑即为笛卡尔哲学的第一原理，其它一切的真...

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">0有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_6403449_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_6403449_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>





